        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 3:51PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 350 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms with torrential
rainfall along a line extending from 5 miles southeast of Columbus to
12 miles northeast of Greenville Downtown to 16 miles southwest of
Spartanburg, and moving east at 30 mph.

Locations to be impacted include...
Spartanburg, Boiling Springs SC, Woodruff, Duncan, Lyman, Pacolet,
Landrum, Cowpens, Wellford, and Inman.

In addition to intense lightning and gusty wind, very heavy rainfall
rates up to 2 inches per hour will be possible in these areas.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent lightning is occurring with these storms. If outdoors, try
to get indoors or into a hard topped vehicle. Otherwise, stay away
from open areas and isolated high objects such as trees. When
indoors, stay away from windows and doors and avoid using wired
electronic devices. Do not take a shower or bath. Try to unplug
unnecessary appliances before the storms approach.</instruction>
